1. *Lanac* je pukao zbog prevelikog opterećenja. (The chain broke due to too much weight.)
2. Potrebno je da *lanac* bude dovoljno čvrst da izdrži teret. (The chain needs to be strong enough to bear the weight.)
3. *Lanac* je bio previše rastegnut pa smo ga morali zameniti. (The chain was too stretched out so we had to replace it.)
4. *Lanac* je korišćen kao vezivo za ogradu. (The chain was used as a binding for the fence.)
5. *Lanac* je jedan od najvažnijih delova mehanizma za pokretanje bicikla. (The chain is one of the most important parts of a bicycle's mechanism.)
6. Radnici su iskoristili *lanac* da podignu teške kutije. (The workers used the chain to lift heavy boxes.)
7. *Lanac* hotela ima restorane u mnogim gradovima. (The hotel chain has restaurants in many cities.)
8. Vozač kamiona je proverio da li je *lanac* pravilno postavljen pre nego što je krenuo. (The truck driver checked if the chain was properly set before he started.)
9. Prijatelji su se uhvatili za *lanac* da bi se spasli od pada niz liticu. (The friends grabbed onto the chain to save themselves from falling down the cliff.)
10. Proizvodni proces u fabrici se sastoji od nekoliko *lanaca* koje su međusobno povezane. (The production process in the factory consists of several chains that are interconnected.)

Note: In Serbian language, nouns decline according to their grammatical cases, therefore, the form of the word "lanac" changes depending on its grammatical role in the sentence.